SIMPLE: effluence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effluence
<hw>Ef"flu*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>effluence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A flowing out, or
emanation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which flows or issues from any body or
substance; issue; efflux.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bright <qex>effluence</qex> of bright essence increate!</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And, as if the gloom of the earth and sky had been but the
<qex>effluence</qex> of these two mortal hearts, it vanished with their
sorrow.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effluency</ent>⟦br⟧
